commit.title: Use ~strict argument consistently in push_context/push_context_set intfs
commit.message:
Use ~strict argument consistently in push_context/push_context_set intfs

One should generally push contexts with ~strict:true when the context is a
monomorphic one (all univs > Set) except for template polymorphic inductives
(>= Prop) and ~strict:false for universe polymorphic ones (>= Set).
